HEADWORD: Sleuthhound
<hw>Sleuth"hound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sleuth</er>, and cf. <er>Slothound</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A hound that tracks animals by the scent; specifically, a
bloodhound.</def> <altsp>[Spelt variously <asp>slouthhound</asp>,
<asp>sluthhound</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

